            </svg>
        </svg>                <img lazy-src="https://www.lamborghini.com/sites/it-en/files/DAM/lamborghini/model/huracan/huracan-evo-rwd/new/car-huracan-block1.png" alt="Detail of Huracán EVO RWD Giallo Belenus left side on a background of the sea "/>
            </div>
            <div class="column small-five small-push-six reset last">
                <div class="boxcontent">
                    <h2><strong>EMOTION</strong> </h2>

                    <p><p>The technological advancements that push Huracán EVO RWD toward the future are counterbalanced by an ever-greater desire to reconnect to the physical, instinctive pleasure of driving. The Huracán EVO RWD embodies the most high-tech return to these origins, and it is dedicated to all those who know they cannot do without technology but embrace the thrill of driving and the joy it can offer. The connoisseur driver holds the reins of the car—controlling it, not the other way around. A strategic game for masters of their car, not for those merely behind the wheel.</p>
</p>

                                    </div>

            </div>

            <div class="image-mobile hidden-over-small"><div style="background-image:url(https://www.lamborghini.com/sites/it-en/files/DAM/lamborghini/model/huracan/huracan-evo-rwd/new/overview-left.jpg)"><img src="https://www.lamborghini.com/sites/it-en/files/DAM/lamborghini/model/huracan/huracan-evo-rwd/new/car-huracan-block1.png"/></div></div>
        </section>






                    <section id="block2" class="stripe row-content block2">
                <div class="column small-seven small-push-one reset last">
                    <div class="boxcontent">
                        <h2><strong>EXTERIOR</strong> </h2>

                        <p><p>Sophisticated aerodynamic solutions are expressed through the iconic Lamborghini Design DNA, which in the Huracán EVO RWD is inspired by the nose of a shark. The design lines emphasize the stance of the car, where the wider front air intake provides an improved aerodynamic system and increased level of efficiency. The characteristic Y-shaped, electric concept headlights adorn the front splitter as an aerodynamic element. Adorning the rear, is an F-Duct spoiler derived from the world of motorsports, which naturally increases downforce through the spoiler's contact with the airflow and harmonizes instinctively with the diffuser below.</p>
</p>
                                            </div>
                </div>

